3098static int copy_context_table(struct intel_iommu *iommu,
3099 struct root_entry *old_re,
3100 struct context_entry **tbl,
3101 int bus, bool ext)
3102{
3103 int tbl_idx, pos = 0, idx, devfn, ret = 0, did;
3104 struct context_entry *new_ce = NULL, ce;
3105 struct context_entry *old_ce = NULL;
3106 struct root_entry re;
3107 phys_addr_t old_ce_phys;
3108
3109 tbl_idx = ext ? bus * 2 : bus;
3110 memcpy(&re, old_re, sizeof(re));
3111
3112 for (devfn = 0; devfn < 256; devfn++) {
3113 /* First calculate the correct index */
3114 idx = (ext ? devfn * 2 : devfn) % 256;
3115
3116 if (idx == 0) {
3117 /* First save what we may have and clean up */
3118 if (new_ce) {
3119 tbl[tbl_idx] = new_ce;
3120 __iommu_flush_cache(iommu, new_ce,
3121 VTD_PAGE_SIZE);
3122 pos = 1;
3123 }
3124
3125 if (old_ce)
3126 iounmap(old_ce);
3127
3128 ret = 0;
3129 if (devfn < 0x80)
3130 old_ce_phys = root_entry_lctp(&re);
3131 else
3132 old_ce_phys = root_entry_uctp(&re);
3133
3134 if (!old_ce_phys) {
3135 if (ext && devfn == 0) {
3136 /* No LCTP, try UCTP */
3137 devfn = 0x7f;
3138 continue;
3139 } else {
3140 goto out;
3141 }
3142 }
3143
3144 ret = -ENOMEM;
3145 old_ce = memremap(old_ce_phys, PAGE_SIZE,
3146 MEMREMAP_WB);
3147 if (!old_ce)
3148 goto out;
3149
3150 new_ce = alloc_pgtable_page(iommu->node);
3151 if (!new_ce)
3152 goto out_unmap;
3153
3154 ret = 0;
3155 }
3156
3157 /* Now copy the context entry */
3158 memcpy(&ce, old_ce + idx, sizeof(ce));
3159
3160 if (!__context_present(&ce))
3161 continue;
3162
3163 did = context_domain_id(&ce);
3164 if (did >= 0 && did < cap_ndoms(iommu->cap))
3165 set_bit(did, iommu->domain_ids);
3166
3167 /*
3168 * We need a marker for copied context entries. This
3169 * marker needs to work for the old format as well as
3170 * for extended context entries.
3171 *
3172 * Bit 67 of the context entry is used. In the old
3173 * format this bit is available to software, in the
3174 * extended format it is the PGE bit, but PGE is ignored
3175 * by HW if PASIDs are disabled (and thus still
3176 * available).
3177 *
3178 * So disable PASIDs first and then mark the entry
3179 * copied. This means that we don't copy PASID
3180 * translations from the old kernel, but this is fine as
3181 * faults there are not fatal.
3182 */
3183 context_clear_pasid_enable(&ce);
3184 context_set_copied(&ce);
3185
3186 new_ce[idx] = ce;
3187 }
3188
3189 tbl[tbl_idx + pos] = new_ce;
3190
3191 __iommu_flush_cache(iommu, new_ce, VTD_PAGE_SIZE);
3192
3193out_unmap:
3194 memunmap(old_ce);
3195
3196out:
3197 return ret;
3198}
3199
3200static int copy_translation_tables(struct intel_iommu *iommu)
3201{
3202 struct context_entry **ctxt_tbls;
3203 struct root_entry *old_rt;
3204 phys_addr_t old_rt_phys;
3205 int ctxt_table_entries;
3206 unsigned long flags;
3207 u64 rtaddr_reg;
3208 int bus, ret;
3209 bool new_ext, ext;
3210
3211 rtaddr_reg = dmar_readq(iommu->reg + DMAR_RTADDR_REG);
3212 ext = !!(rtaddr_reg & DMA_RTADDR_RTT);
3213 new_ext = !!ecap_ecs(iommu->ecap);
3214
3215 /*
3216 * The RTT bit can only be changed when translation is disabled,
3217 * but disabling translation means to open a window for data
3218 * corruption. So bail out and don't copy anything if we would
3219 * have to change the bit.
3220 */
3221 if (new_ext != ext)
3222 return -EINVAL;
3223
3224 old_rt_phys = rtaddr_reg & VTD_PAGE_MASK;
3225 if (!old_rt_phys)
3226 return -EINVAL;
3227
3228 old_rt = memremap(old_rt_phys, PAGE_SIZE, MEMREMAP_WB);
3229 if (!old_rt)
3230 return -ENOMEM;
3231
3232 /* This is too big for the stack - allocate it from slab */
3233 ctxt_table_entries = ext ? 512 : 256;
3234 ret = -ENOMEM;
3235 ctxt_tbls = kcalloc(ctxt_table_entries, sizeof(void *), GFP_KERNEL);
3236 if (!ctxt_tbls)
3237 goto out_unmap;
3238
3239 for (bus = 0; bus < 256; bus++) {
3240 ret = copy_context_table(iommu, &old_rt[bus],
3241 ctxt_tbls, bus, ext);
3242 if (ret) {
3243 pr_err("%s: Failed to copy context table for bus %d\n",
3244 iommu->name, bus);
3245 continue;
3246 }
3247 }
3248
3249 spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu->lock, flags);
3250
3251 /* Context tables are copied, now write them to the root_entry table */
3252 for (bus = 0; bus < 256; bus++) {
3253 int idx = ext ? bus * 2 : bus;
3254 u64 val;
3255
3256 if (ctxt_tbls[idx]) {
3257 val = virt_to_phys(ctxt_tbls[idx]) | 1;
3258 iommu->root_entry[bus].lo = val;
3259 }
3260
3261 if (!ext || !ctxt_tbls[idx + 1])
3262 continue;
3263
3264 val = virt_to_phys(ctxt_tbls[idx + 1]) | 1;
3265 iommu->root_entry[bus].hi = val;
3266 }
3267
3268 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu->lock, flags);
3269
3270 kfree(ctxt_tbls);
3271
3272 __iommu_flush_cache(iommu, iommu->root_entry, PAGE_SIZE);
3273
3274 ret = 0;
3275
3276out_unmap:
3277 memunmap(old_rt);
3278
3279 return ret;
3280}
3281
3282static int __init init_dmars(void)
3283{
3284 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
3285 struct dmar_rmrr_unit *rmrr;
3286 bool copied_tables = false;
3287 struct device *dev;
3288 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
3289 int i, ret;
3290
3291 /*
3292 * for each drhd
3293 * allocate root
3294 * initialize and program root entry to not present
3295 * endfor
3296 */
3297 for_each_drhd_unit(drhd) {
3298 /*
3299 * lock not needed as this is only incremented in the single
3300 * threaded kernel __init code path all other access are read
3301 * only
3302 */
3303 if (g_num_of_iommus < DMAR_UNITS_SUPPORTED) {
3304 g_num_of_iommus++;
3305 continue;
3306 }
3307 pr_err_once("Exceeded %d IOMMUs\n", DMAR_UNITS_SUPPORTED);
3308 }
3309
3310 /* Preallocate enough resources for IOMMU hot-addition */
3311 if (g_num_of_iommus < DMAR_UNITS_SUPPORTED)
3312 g_num_of_iommus = DMAR_UNITS_SUPPORTED;
3313
3314 g_iommus = kcalloc(g_num_of_iommus, sizeof(struct intel_iommu *),
3315 GFP_KERNEL);
3316 if (!g_iommus) {
3317 pr_err("Allocating global iommu array failed\n");
3318 ret = -ENOMEM;
3319 goto error;
3320 }
3321
3322 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
3323 g_iommus[iommu->seq_id] = iommu;
3324
3325 intel_iommu_init_qi(iommu);
3326
3327 ret = iommu_init_domains(iommu);
3328 if (ret)
3329 goto free_iommu;
3330
3331 init_translation_status(iommu);
3332
3333 if (translation_pre_enabled(iommu) && !is_kdump_kernel()) {
3334 iommu_disable_translation(iommu);
3335 clear_translation_pre_enabled(iommu);
3336 pr_warn("Translation was enabled for %s but we are not in kdump mode\n",
3337 iommu->name);
3338 }
3339
3340 /*
3341 * TBD:
3342 * we could share the same root & context tables
3343 * among all IOMMU's. Need to Split it later.
3344 */
3345 ret = iommu_alloc_root_entry(iommu);
3346 if (ret)
3347 goto free_iommu;
3348
3349 if (translation_pre_enabled(iommu)) {
3350 pr_info("Translation already enabled - trying to copy translation structures\n");
3351
3352 ret = copy_translation_tables(iommu);
3353 if (ret) {
3354 /*
3355 * We found the IOMMU with translation
3356 * enabled - but failed to copy over the
3357 * old root-entry table. Try to proceed
3358 * by disabling translation now and
3359 * allocating a clean root-entry table.
3360 * This might cause DMAR faults, but
3361 * probably the dump will still succeed.
3362 */
3363 pr_err("Failed to copy translation tables from previous kernel for %s\n",
3364 iommu->name);
3365 iommu_disable_translation(iommu);
3366 clear_translation_pre_enabled(iommu);
3367 } else {
3368 pr_info("Copied translation tables from previous kernel for %s\n",
3369 iommu->name);
3370 copied_tables = true;
3371 }
3372 }
3373
3374 if (!ecap_pass_through(iommu->ecap))
3375 hw_pass_through = 0;
3376#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_SVM
3377 if (pasid_enabled(iommu))
3378 intel_svm_alloc_pasid_tables(iommu);
3379#endif
3380 }
3381
3382 /*
3383 * Now that qi is enabled on all iommus, set the root entry and flush
3384 * caches. This is required on some Intel X58 chipsets, otherwise the
3385 * flush_context function will loop forever and the boot hangs.
3386 */
3387 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
3388 iommu_flush_write_buffer(iommu);
3389 iommu_set_root_entry(iommu);
3390 iommu->flush.flush_context(iommu, 0, 0, 0, DMA_CCMD_GLOBAL_INVL);
3391 iommu->flush.flush_iotlb(iommu, 0, 0, 0, DMA_TLB_GLOBAL_FLUSH);
3392 }
3393
3394 if (iommu_pass_through)
3395 iommu_identity_mapping |= IDENTMAP_ALL;
3396
3397#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_BROKEN_GFX_WA
3398 iommu_identity_mapping |= IDENTMAP_GFX;
3399#endif
3400
3401 check_tylersburg_isoch();
3402
3403 if (iommu_identity_mapping) {
3404 ret = si_domain_init(hw_pass_through);
3405 if (ret)
3406 goto free_iommu;
3407 }
3408
3409
3410 /*
3411 * If we copied translations from a previous kernel in the kdump
3412 * case, we can not assign the devices to domains now, as that
3413 * would eliminate the old mappings. So skip this part and defer
3414 * the assignment to device driver initialization time.
3415 */
3416 if (copied_tables)
3417 goto domains_done;
3418
3419 /*
3420 * If pass through is not set or not enabled, setup context entries for
3421 * identity mappings for rmrr, gfx, and isa and may fall back to static
3422 * identity mapping if iommu_identity_mapping is set.
3423 */
3424 if (iommu_identity_mapping) {
3425 ret = iommu_prepare_static_identity_mapping(hw_pass_through);
3426 if (ret) {
3427 pr_crit("Failed to setup IOMMU pass-through\n");
3428 goto free_iommu;
3429 }
3430 }
3431 /*
3432 * For each rmrr
3433 * for each dev attached to rmrr
3434 * do
3435 * locate drhd for dev, alloc domain for dev
3436 * allocate free domain
3437 * allocate page table entries for rmrr
3438 * if context not allocated for bus
3439 * allocate and init context
3440 * set present in root table for this bus
3441 * init context with domain, translation etc
3442 * endfor
3443 * endfor
3444 */
3445 pr_info("Setting RMRR:\n");
3446 for_each_rmrr_units(rmrr) {
3447 /* some BIOS lists non-exist devices in DMAR table. */
3448 for_each_active_dev_scope(rmrr->devices, rmrr->devices_cnt,
3449 i, dev) {
3450 ret = iommu_prepare_rmrr_dev(rmrr, dev);
3451 if (ret)
3452 pr_err("Mapping reserved region failed\n");
3453 }
3454 }
3455
3456 iommu_prepare_isa();
3457
3458domains_done:
3459
3460 /*
3461 * for each drhd
3462 * enable fault log
3463 * global invalidate context cache
3464 * global invalidate iotlb
3465 * enable translation
3466 */
3467 for_each_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
3468 if (drhd->ignored) {
3469 /*
3470 * we always have to disable PMRs or DMA may fail on
3471 * this device
3472 */
3473 if (force_on)
3474 iommu_disable_protect_mem_regions(iommu);
3475 continue;
3476 }
3477
3478 iommu_flush_write_buffer(iommu);
3479
3480#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_SVM
3481 if (pasid_enabled(iommu) && ecap_prs(iommu->ecap)) {
3482 ret = intel_svm_enable_prq(iommu);
3483 if (ret)
3484 goto free_iommu;
3485 }
3486#endif
3487 ret = dmar_set_interrupt(iommu);
3488 if (ret)
3489 goto free_iommu;
3490
3491 if (!translation_pre_enabled(iommu))
3492 iommu_enable_translation(iommu);
3493
3494 iommu_disable_protect_mem_regions(iommu);
3495 }
3496
3497 return 0;
3498
3499free_iommu:
3500 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
3501 disable_dmar_iommu(iommu);
3502 free_dmar_iommu(iommu);
3503 }
3504
3505 kfree(g_iommus);
3506
3507error:
3508 return ret;
3509}
3510
3511/* This takes a number of _MM_ pages, not VTD pages */
3512static unsigned long intel_alloc_iova(struct device *dev,
3513 struct dmar_domain *domain,
3514 unsigned long nrpages, uint64_t dma_mask)
3515{
3516 unsigned long iova_pfn = 0;
3517
3518 /* Restrict dma_mask to the width that the iommu can handle */
3519 dma_mask = min_t(uint64_t, DOMAIN_MAX_ADDR(domain->gaw), dma_mask);
3520 /* Ensure we reserve the whole size-aligned region */
3521 nrpages = __roundup_pow_of_two(nrpages);
3522
3523 if (!dmar_forcedac && dma_mask > DMA_BIT_MASK(32)) {
3524 /*
3525 * First try to allocate an io virtual address in
3526 * DMA_BIT_MASK(32) and if that fails then try allocating
3527 * from higher range
3528 */
3529 iova_pfn = alloc_iova_fast(&domain->iovad, nrpages,
3530 IOVA_PFN(DMA_BIT_MASK(32)), false);
3531 if (iova_pfn)
3532 return iova_pfn;
3533 }
3534 iova_pfn = alloc_iova_fast(&domain->iovad, nrpages,
3535 IOVA_PFN(dma_mask), true);
3536 if (unlikely(!iova_pfn)) {
3537 pr_err("Allocating %ld-page iova for %s failed",
3538 nrpages, dev_name(dev));
3539 return 0;
3540 }
3541
3542 return iova_pfn;
3543}
3544
3545static struct dmar_domain *get_valid_domain_for_dev(struct device *dev)
3546{
3547 struct dmar_domain *domain, *tmp;
3548 struct dmar_rmrr_unit *rmrr;
3549 struct device *i_dev;
3550 int i, ret;
3551
3552 domain = find_domain(dev);
3553 if (domain)
3554 goto out;
3555
3556 domain = find_or_alloc_domain(dev, DEFAULT_DOMAIN_ADDRESS_WIDTH);
3557 if (!domain)
3558 goto out;
3559
3560 /* We have a new domain - setup possible RMRRs for the device */
3561 rcu_read_lock();
3562 for_each_rmrr_units(rmrr) {
3563 for_each_active_dev_scope(rmrr->devices, rmrr->devices_cnt,
3564 i, i_dev) {
3565 if (i_dev != dev)
3566 continue;
3567
3568 ret = domain_prepare_identity_map(dev, domain,
3569 rmrr->base_address,
3570 rmrr->end_address);
3571 if (ret)
3572 dev_err(dev, "Mapping reserved region failed\n");
3573 }
3574 }
3575 rcu_read_unlock();
3576
3577 tmp = set_domain_for_dev(dev, domain);
3578 if (!tmp || domain != tmp) {
3579 domain_exit(domain);
3580 domain = tmp;
3581 }
3582
3583out:
3584
3585 if (!domain)
3586 pr_err("Allocating domain for %s failed\n", dev_name(dev));
3587
3588
3589 return domain;
3590}
3591
3592/* Check if the dev needs to go through non-identity map and unmap process.*/
3593static int iommu_no_mapping(struct device *dev)
3594{
3595 int found;
3596
3597 if (iommu_dummy(dev))
3598 return 1;
3599
3600 if (!iommu_identity_mapping)
3601 return 0;
3602
3603 found = identity_mapping(dev);
3604 if (found) {
3605 if (iommu_should_identity_map(dev, 0))
3606 return 1;
3607 else {
3608 /*
3609 * 32 bit DMA is removed from si_domain and fall back
3610 * to non-identity mapping.
3611 */
3612 dmar_remove_one_dev_info(si_domain, dev);
3613 pr_info("32bit %s uses non-identity mapping\n",
3614 dev_name(dev));
3615 return 0;
3616 }
3617 } else {
3618 /*
3619 * In case of a detached 64 bit DMA device from vm, the device
3620 * is put into si_domain for identity mapping.
3621 */
3622 if (iommu_should_identity_map(dev, 0)) {
3623 int ret;
3624 ret = domain_add_dev_info(si_domain, dev);
3625 if (!ret) {
3626 pr_info("64bit %s uses identity mapping\n",
3627 dev_name(dev));
3628 return 1;
3629 }
3630 }
3631 }
3632
3633 return 0;
3634}
3635
3636static dma_addr_t __intel_map_single(struct device *dev, phys_addr_t paddr,
3637 size_t size, int dir, u64 dma_mask)
3638{
3639 struct dmar_domain *domain;
3640 phys_addr_t start_paddr;
3641 unsigned long iova_pfn;
3642 int prot = 0;
3643 int ret;
3644 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
3645 unsigned long paddr_pfn = paddr >> PAGE_SHIFT;
3646
3647 BUG_ON(dir == DMA_NONE);
3648
3649 if (iommu_no_mapping(dev))
3650 return paddr;
3651
3652 domain = get_valid_domain_for_dev(dev);
3653 if (!domain)
3654 return 0;
3655
3656 iommu = domain_get_iommu(domain);
3657 size = aligned_nrpages(paddr, size);
3658
3659 iova_pfn = intel_alloc_iova(dev, domain, dma_to_mm_pfn(size), dma_mask);
3660 if (!iova_pfn)
3661 goto error;
3662
3663 /*
3664 * Check if DMAR supports zero-length reads on write only
3665 * mappings..
3666 */
3667 if (dir == DMA_TO_DEVICE || dir == DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL || \
3668 !cap_zlr(iommu->cap))
3669 prot |= DMA_PTE_READ;
3670 if (dir == DMA_FROM_DEVICE || dir == DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL)
3671 prot |= DMA_PTE_WRITE;
3672 /*
3673 * paddr - (paddr + size) might be partial page, we should map the whole
3674 * page. Note: if two part of one page are separately mapped, we
3675 * might have two guest_addr mapping to the same host paddr, but this
3676 * is not a big problem
3677 */
3678 ret = domain_pfn_mapping(domain, mm_to_dma_pfn(iova_pfn),
3679 mm_to_dma_pfn(paddr_pfn), size, prot);
3680 if (ret)
3681 goto error;
3682
3683 start_paddr = (phys_addr_t)iova_pfn << PAGE_SHIFT;
3684 start_paddr += paddr & ~PAGE_MASK;
3685 return start_paddr;
3686
3687error:
3688 if (iova_pfn)
3689 free_iova_fast(&domain->iovad, iova_pfn, dma_to_mm_pfn(size));
3690 pr_err("Device %s request: %zx@%llx dir %d --- failed\n",
3691 dev_name(dev), size, (unsigned long long)paddr, dir);
3692 return 0;
3693}
3694
3695static dma_addr_t intel_map_page(struct device *dev, struct page *page,
3696 unsigned long offset, size_t size,
3697 enum dma_data_direction dir,
3698 unsigned long attrs)
3699{
3700 return __intel_map_single(dev, page_to_phys(page) + offset, size,
3701 dir, *dev->dma_mask);
3702}
3703
3704static void intel_unmap(struct device *dev, dma_addr_t dev_addr, size_t size)
3705{
3706 struct dmar_domain *domain;
3707 unsigned long start_pfn, last_pfn;
3708 unsigned long nrpages;
3709 unsigned long iova_pfn;
3710 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
3711 struct page *freelist;
3712
3713 if (iommu_no_mapping(dev))
3714 return;
3715
3716 domain = find_domain(dev);
3717 BUG_ON(!domain);
3718
3719 iommu = domain_get_iommu(domain);
3720
3721 iova_pfn = IOVA_PFN(dev_addr);
3722
3723 nrpages = aligned_nrpages(dev_addr, size);
3724 start_pfn = mm_to_dma_pfn(iova_pfn);
3725 last_pfn = start_pfn + nrpages - 1;
3726
3727 pr_debug("Device %s unmapping: pfn %lx-%lx\n",
3728 dev_name(dev), start_pfn, last_pfn);
3729
3730 freelist = domain_unmap(domain, start_pfn, last_pfn);
3731
3732 if (intel_iommu_strict) {
3733 iommu_flush_iotlb_psi(iommu, domain, start_pfn,
3734 nrpages, !freelist, 0);
3735 /* free iova */
3736 free_iova_fast(&domain->iovad, iova_pfn, dma_to_mm_pfn(nrpages));
3737 dma_free_pagelist(freelist);
3738 } else {
3739 queue_iova(&domain->iovad, iova_pfn, nrpages,
3740 (unsigned long)freelist);
3741 /*
3742 * queue up the release of the unmap to save the 1/6th of the
3743 * cpu used up by the iotlb flush operation...
3744 */
3745 }
3746}
3747
3748static void intel_unmap_page(struct device *dev, dma_addr_t dev_addr,
3749 size_t size, enum dma_data_direction dir,
3750 unsigned long attrs)
3751{
3752 intel_unmap(dev, dev_addr, size);
3753}
3754
3755static void *intel_alloc_coherent(struct device *dev, size_t size,
3756 dma_addr_t *dma_handle, gfp_t flags,
3757 unsigned long attrs)
3758{
3759 struct page *page = NULL;
3760 int order;
3761
3762 size = PAGE_ALIGN(size);
3763 order = get_order(size);
3764
3765 if (!iommu_no_mapping(dev))
3766 flags &= ~(GFP_DMA | GFP_DMA32);
3767 else if (dev->coherent_dma_mask < dma_get_required_mask(dev)) {
3768 if (dev->coherent_dma_mask < DMA_BIT_MASK(32))
3769 flags |= GFP_DMA;
3770 else
3771 flags |= GFP_DMA32;
3772 }
3773
3774 if (gfpflags_allow_blocking(flags)) {
3775 unsigned int count = size >> PAGE_SHIFT;
3776
3777 page = dma_alloc_from_contiguous(dev, count, order, flags);
3778 if (page && iommu_no_mapping(dev) &&
3779 page_to_phys(page) + size > dev->coherent_dma_mask) {
3780 dma_release_from_contiguous(dev, page, count);
3781 page = NULL;
3782 }
3783 }
3784
3785 if (!page)
3786 page = alloc_pages(flags, order);
3787 if (!page)
3788 return NULL;
3789 memset(page_address(page), 0, size);
3790
3791 *dma_handle = __intel_map_single(dev, page_to_phys(page), size,
3792 DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL,
3793 dev->coherent_dma_mask);
3794 if (*dma_handle)
3795 return page_address(page);
3796 if (!dma_release_from_contiguous(dev, page, size >> PAGE_SHIFT))
3797 __free_pages(page, order);
3798
3799 return NULL;
3800}
3801
3802static void intel_free_coherent(struct device *dev, size_t size, void *vaddr,
3803 dma_addr_t dma_handle, unsigned long attrs)
3804{
3805 int order;
3806 struct page *page = virt_to_page(vaddr);
3807
3808 size = PAGE_ALIGN(size);
3809 order = get_order(size);
3810
3811 intel_unmap(dev, dma_handle, size);
3812 if (!dma_release_from_contiguous(dev, page, size >> PAGE_SHIFT))
3813 __free_pages(page, order);
3814}

3846static int intel_map_sg(struct device *dev, struct scatterlist *sglist, int nelems,
3847 enum dma_data_direction dir, unsigned long attrs)
3848{
3849 int i;
3850 struct dmar_domain *domain;
3851 size_t size = 0;
3852 int prot = 0;
3853 unsigned long iova_pfn;
3854 int ret;
3855 struct scatterlist *sg;
3856 unsigned long start_vpfn;
3857 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
3858
3859 BUG_ON(dir == DMA_NONE);
3860 if (iommu_no_mapping(dev))
3861 return intel_nontranslate_map_sg(dev, sglist, nelems, dir);
3862
3863 domain = get_valid_domain_for_dev(dev);
3864 if (!domain)
3865 return 0;
3866
3867 iommu = domain_get_iommu(domain);
3868
3869 for_each_sg(sglist, sg, nelems, i)
3870 size += aligned_nrpages(sg->offset, sg->length);
3871
3872 iova_pfn = intel_alloc_iova(dev, domain, dma_to_mm_pfn(size),
3873 *dev->dma_mask);
3874 if (!iova_pfn) {
3875 sglist->dma_length = 0;
3876 return 0;
3877 }
3878
3879 /*
3880 * Check if DMAR supports zero-length reads on write only
3881 * mappings..
3882 */
3883 if (dir == DMA_TO_DEVICE || dir == DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL || \
3884 !cap_zlr(iommu->cap))
3885 prot |= DMA_PTE_READ;
3886 if (dir == DMA_FROM_DEVICE || dir == DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL)
3887 prot |= DMA_PTE_WRITE;
3888
3889 start_vpfn = mm_to_dma_pfn(iova_pfn);
3890
3891 ret = domain_sg_mapping(domain, start_vpfn, sglist, size, prot);
3892 if (unlikely(ret)) {
3893 dma_pte_free_pagetable(domain, start_vpfn,
3894 start_vpfn + size - 1,
3895 agaw_to_level(domain->agaw) + 1);
3896 free_iova_fast(&domain->iovad, iova_pfn, dma_to_mm_pfn(size));
3897 return 0;
3898 }
3899
3900 return nelems;
3901}

3985static void quirk_ioat_snb_local_iommu(struct pci_dev *pdev)
3986{
3987 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
3988 u32 vtbar;
3989 int rc;
3990
3991 /* We know that this device on this chipset has its own IOMMU.
3992 * If we find it under a different IOMMU, then the BIOS is lying
3993 * to us. Hope that the IOMMU for this device is actually
3994 * disabled, and it needs no translation...
3995 */
3996 rc = pci_bus_read_config_dword(pdev->bus, PCI_DEVFN(0, 0), 0xb0, &vtbar);
3997 if (rc) {
3998 /* "can't" happen */
3999 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "failed to run vt-d quirk\n");
4000 return;
4001 }
4002 vtbar &= 0xffff0000;
4003
4004 /* we know that the this iommu should be at offset 0xa000 from vtbar */
4005 drhd = dmar_find_matched_drhd_unit(pdev);
4006 if (WARN_TAINT_ONCE(!drhd || drhd->reg_base_addr - vtbar != 0xa000,
4007 TAINT_FIRMWARE_WORKAROUND,
4008 "BIOS assigned incorrect VT-d unit for Intel(R) QuickData Technology device\n"))
4009 pdev->dev.archdata.iommu = DUMMY_DEVICE_DOMAIN_INFO;
4010}
4011DECLARE_PCI_FIXUP_ENABLE(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL, PCI_DEVICE_ID_INTEL_IOAT_SNB, quirk_ioat_snb_local_iommu);

4013static void __init init_no_remapping_devices(void)
4014{
4015 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
4016 struct device *dev;
4017 int i;
4018
4019 for_each_drhd_unit(drhd) {
4020 if (!drhd->include_all) {
4021 for_each_active_dev_scope(drhd->devices,
4022 drhd->devices_cnt, i, dev)
4023 break;
4024 /* ignore DMAR unit if no devices exist */
4025 if (i == drhd->devices_cnt)
4026 drhd->ignored = 1;
4027 }
4028 }
4029
4030 for_each_active_drhd_unit(drhd) {
4031 if (drhd->include_all)
4032 continue;
4033
4034 for_each_active_dev_scope(drhd->devices,
4035 drhd->devices_cnt, i, dev)
4036 if (!dev_is_pci(dev) || !IS_GFX_DEVICE(to_pci_dev(dev)))
4037 break;
4038 if (i < drhd->devices_cnt)
4039 continue;
4040
4041 /* This IOMMU has *only* gfx devices. Either bypass it or
4042 set the gfx_mapped flag, as appropriate */
4043 if (dmar_map_gfx) {
4044 intel_iommu_gfx_mapped = 1;
4045 } else {
4046 drhd->ignored = 1;
4047 for_each_active_dev_scope(drhd->devices,
4048 drhd->devices_cnt, i, dev)
4049 dev->archdata.iommu = DUMMY_DEVICE_DOMAIN_INFO;
4050 }
4051 }
4052}

4101
4102static int iommu_suspend(void)
4103{
4104 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
4105 struct intel_iommu *iommu = NULL;
4106 unsigned long flag;
4107
4108 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
4109 iommu->iommu_state = kcalloc(MAX_SR_DMAR_REGS, sizeof(u32),
4110 GFP_ATOMIC);
4111 if (!iommu->iommu_state)
4112 goto nomem;
4113 }
4114
4115 iommu_flush_all();
4116
4117 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
4118 iommu_disable_translation(iommu);
4119
4120 raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu->register_lock, flag);
4121
4122 iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FECTL_REG] =
4123 readl(iommu->reg + DMAR_FECTL_REG);
4124 iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEDATA_REG] =
4125 readl(iommu->reg + DMAR_FEDATA_REG);
4126 iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEADDR_REG] =
4127 readl(iommu->reg + DMAR_FEADDR_REG);
4128 iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEUADDR_REG] =
4129 readl(iommu->reg + DMAR_FEUADDR_REG);
4130
4131 raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu->register_lock, flag);
4132 }
4133 return 0;
4134
4135nomem:
4136 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd)
4137 kfree(iommu->iommu_state);
4138
4139 return -ENOMEM;
4140}
4141
4142static void iommu_resume(void)
4143{
4144 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
4145 struct intel_iommu *iommu = NULL;
4146 unsigned long flag;
4147
4148 if (init_iommu_hw()) {
4149 if (force_on)
4150 panic("tboot: IOMMU setup failed, DMAR can not resume!\n");
4151 else
4152 WARN(1, "IOMMU setup failed, DMAR can not resume!\n");
4153 return;
4154 }
4155
4156 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
4157
4158 raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu->register_lock, flag);
4159
4160 writel(iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FECTL_REG],
4161 iommu->reg + DMAR_FECTL_REG);
4162 writel(iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEDATA_REG],
4163 iommu->reg + DMAR_FEDATA_REG);
4164 writel(iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEADDR_REG],
4165 iommu->reg + DMAR_FEADDR_REG);
4166 writel(iommu->iommu_state[SR_DMAR_FEUADDR_REG],
4167 iommu->reg + DMAR_FEUADDR_REG);
4168
4169 raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu->register_lock, flag);
4170 }
4171
4172 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd)
4173 kfree(iommu->iommu_state);
4174}

4190
4191int __init dmar_parse_one_rmrr(struct acpi_dmar_header *header, void *arg)
4192{
4193 struct acpi_dmar_reserved_memory *rmrr;
4194 int prot = DMA_PTE_READ|DMA_PTE_WRITE;
4195 struct dmar_rmrr_unit *rmrru;
4196 size_t length;
4197
4198 rmrru = kzalloc(sizeof(*rmrru), GFP_KERNEL);
4199 if (!rmrru)
4200 goto out;
4201
4202 rmrru->hdr = header;
4203 rmrr = (struct acpi_dmar_reserved_memory *)header;
4204 rmrru->base_address = rmrr->base_address;
4205 rmrru->end_address = rmrr->end_address;
4206
4207 length = rmrr->end_address - rmrr->base_address + 1;
4208 rmrru->resv = iommu_alloc_resv_region(rmrr->base_address, length, prot,
4209 IOMMU_RESV_DIRECT);
4210 if (!rmrru->resv)
4211 goto free_rmrru;
4212
4213 rmrru->devices = dmar_alloc_dev_scope((void *)(rmrr + 1),
4214 ((void *)rmrr) + rmrr->header.length,
4215 &rmrru->devices_cnt);
4216 if (rmrru->devices_cnt && rmrru->devices == NULL)
4217 goto free_all;
4218
4219 list_add(&rmrru->list, &dmar_rmrr_units);
4220
4221 return 0;
4222free_all:
4223 kfree(rmrru->resv);
4224free_rmrru:
4225 kfree(rmrru);
4226out:
4227 return -ENOMEM;
4228}
4229
4230static struct dmar_atsr_unit *dmar_find_atsr(struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr)
4231{
4232 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4233 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *tmp;
4234
4235 list_for_each_entry_rcu(atsru, &dmar_atsr_units, list) {
4236 tmp = (struct acpi_dmar_atsr *)atsru->hdr;
4237 if (atsr->segment != tmp->segment)
4238 continue;
4239 if (atsr->header.length != tmp->header.length)
4240 continue;
4241 if (memcmp(atsr, tmp, atsr->header.length) == 0)
4242 return atsru;
4243 }
4244
4245 return NULL;
4246}
4247
4248int dmar_parse_one_atsr(struct acpi_dmar_header *hdr, void *arg)
4249{
4250 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr;
4251 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4252
4253 if (system_state >= SYSTEM_RUNNING && !intel_iommu_enabled)
4254 return 0;
4255
4256 atsr = container_of(hdr, struct acpi_dmar_atsr, header);
4257 atsru = dmar_find_atsr(atsr);
4258 if (atsru)
4259 return 0;
4260
4261 atsru = kzalloc(sizeof(*atsru) + hdr->length, GFP_KERNEL);
4262 if (!atsru)
4263 return -ENOMEM;
4264
4265 /*
4266 * If memory is allocated from slab by ACPI _DSM method, we need to
4267 * copy the memory content because the memory buffer will be freed
4268 * on return.
4269 */
4270 atsru->hdr = (void *)(atsru + 1);
4271 memcpy(atsru->hdr, hdr, hdr->length);
4272 atsru->include_all = atsr->flags & 0x1;
4273 if (!atsru->include_all) {
4274 atsru->devices = dmar_alloc_dev_scope((void *)(atsr + 1),
4275 (void *)atsr + atsr->header.length,
4276 &atsru->devices_cnt);
4277 if (atsru->devices_cnt && atsru->devices == NULL) {
4278 kfree(atsru);
4279 return -ENOMEM;
4280 }
4281 }
4282
4283 list_add_rcu(&atsru->list, &dmar_atsr_units);
4284
4285 return 0;
4286}
4287
4288static void intel_iommu_free_atsr(struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru)
4289{
4290 dmar_free_dev_scope(&atsru->devices, &atsru->devices_cnt);
4291 kfree(atsru);
4292}
4293
4294int dmar_release_one_atsr(struct acpi_dmar_header *hdr, void *arg)
4295{
4296 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr;
4297 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4298
4299 atsr = container_of(hdr, struct acpi_dmar_atsr, header);
4300 atsru = dmar_find_atsr(atsr);
4301 if (atsru) {
4302 list_del_rcu(&atsru->list);
4303 synchronize_rcu();
4304 intel_iommu_free_atsr(atsru);
4305 }
4306
4307 return 0;
4308}
4309
4310int dmar_check_one_atsr(struct acpi_dmar_header *hdr, void *arg)
4311{
4312 int i;
4313 struct device *dev;
4314 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr;
4315 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4316
4317 atsr = container_of(hdr, struct acpi_dmar_atsr, header);
4318 atsru = dmar_find_atsr(atsr);
4319 if (!atsru)
4320 return 0;
4321
4322 if (!atsru->include_all && atsru->devices && atsru->devices_cnt) {
4323 for_each_active_dev_scope(atsru->devices, atsru->devices_cnt,
4324 i, dev)
4325 return -EBUSY;
4326 }
4327
4328 return 0;
4329}
4330
4331static int intel_iommu_add(struct dmar_drhd_unit *dmaru)
4332{
4333 int sp, ret = 0;
4334 struct intel_iommu *iommu = dmaru->iommu;
4335
4336 if (g_iommus[iommu->seq_id])
4337 return 0;
4338
4339 if (hw_pass_through && !ecap_pass_through(iommu->ecap)) {
4340 pr_warn("%s: Doesn't support hardware pass through.\n",
4341 iommu->name);
4342 return -ENXIO;
4343 }
4344 if (!ecap_sc_support(iommu->ecap) &&
4345 domain_update_iommu_snooping(iommu)) {
4346 pr_warn("%s: Doesn't support snooping.\n",
4347 iommu->name);
4348 return -ENXIO;
4349 }
4350 sp = domain_update_iommu_superpage(iommu) - 1;
4351 if (sp >= 0 && !(cap_super_page_val(iommu->cap) & (1 << sp))) {
4352 pr_warn("%s: Doesn't support large page.\n",
4353 iommu->name);
4354 return -ENXIO;
4355 }
4356
4357 /*
4358 * Disable translation if already enabled prior to OS handover.
4359 */
4360 if (iommu->gcmd & DMA_GCMD_TE)
4361 iommu_disable_translation(iommu);
4362
4363 g_iommus[iommu->seq_id] = iommu;
4364 ret = iommu_init_domains(iommu);
4365 if (ret == 0)
4366 ret = iommu_alloc_root_entry(iommu);
4367 if (ret)
4368 goto out;
4369
4370#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_SVM
4371 if (pasid_enabled(iommu))
4372 intel_svm_alloc_pasid_tables(iommu);
4373#endif
4374
4375 if (dmaru->ignored) {
4376 /*
4377 * we always have to disable PMRs or DMA may fail on this device
4378 */
4379 if (force_on)
4380 iommu_disable_protect_mem_regions(iommu);
4381 return 0;
4382 }
4383
4384 intel_iommu_init_qi(iommu);
4385 iommu_flush_write_buffer(iommu);
4386
4387#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_SVM
4388 if (pasid_enabled(iommu) && ecap_prs(iommu->ecap)) {
4389 ret = intel_svm_enable_prq(iommu);
4390 if (ret)
4391 goto disable_iommu;
4392 }
4393#endif
4394 ret = dmar_set_interrupt(iommu);
4395 if (ret)
4396 goto disable_iommu;
4397
4398 iommu_set_root_entry(iommu);
4399 iommu->flush.flush_context(iommu, 0, 0, 0, DMA_CCMD_GLOBAL_INVL);
4400 iommu->flush.flush_iotlb(iommu, 0, 0, 0, DMA_TLB_GLOBAL_FLUSH);
4401 iommu_enable_translation(iommu);
4402
4403 iommu_disable_protect_mem_regions(iommu);
4404 return 0;
4405
4406disable_iommu:
4407 disable_dmar_iommu(iommu);
4408out:
4409 free_dmar_iommu(iommu);
4410 return ret;
4411}
4412
4413int dmar_iommu_hotplug(struct dmar_drhd_unit *dmaru, bool insert)
4414{
4415 int ret = 0;
4416 struct intel_iommu *iommu = dmaru->iommu;
4417
4418 if (!intel_iommu_enabled)
4419 return 0;
4420 if (iommu == NULL)
4421 return -EINVAL;
4422
4423 if (insert) {
4424 ret = intel_iommu_add(dmaru);
4425 } else {
4426 disable_dmar_iommu(iommu);
4427 free_dmar_iommu(iommu);
4428 }
4429
4430 return ret;
4431}

4451int dmar_find_matched_atsr_unit(struct pci_dev *dev)
4452{
4453 int i, ret = 1;
4454 struct pci_bus *bus;
4455 struct pci_dev *bridge = NULL;
4456 struct device *tmp;
4457 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr;
4458 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4459
4460 dev = pci_physfn(dev);
4461 for (bus = dev->bus; bus; bus = bus->parent) {
4462 bridge = bus->self;
4463 /* If it's an integrated device, allow ATS */
4464 if (!bridge)
4465 return 1;
4466 /* Connected via non-PCIe: no ATS */
4467 if (!pci_is_pcie(bridge) ||
4468 pci_pcie_type(bridge) == PCI_EXP_TYPE_PCI_BRIDGE)
4469 return 0;
4470 /* If we found the root port, look it up in the ATSR */
4471 if (pci_pcie_type(bridge) == PCI_EXP_TYPE_ROOT_PORT)
4472 break;
4473 }
4474
4475 rcu_read_lock();
4476 list_for_each_entry_rcu(atsru, &dmar_atsr_units, list) {
4477 atsr = container_of(atsru->hdr, struct acpi_dmar_atsr, header);
4478 if (atsr->segment != pci_domain_nr(dev->bus))
4479 continue;
4480
4481 for_each_dev_scope(atsru->devices, atsru->devices_cnt, i, tmp)
4482 if (tmp == &bridge->dev)
4483 goto out;
4484
4485 if (atsru->include_all)
4486 goto out;
4487 }
4488 ret = 0;
4489out:
4490 rcu_read_unlock();
4491
4492 return ret;
4493}
4494
4495int dmar_iommu_notify_scope_dev(struct dmar_pci_notify_info *info)
4496{
4497 int ret = 0;
4498 struct dmar_rmrr_unit *rmrru;
4499 struct dmar_atsr_unit *atsru;
4500 struct acpi_dmar_atsr *atsr;
4501 struct acpi_dmar_reserved_memory *rmrr;
4502
4503 if (!intel_iommu_enabled && system_state >= SYSTEM_RUNNING)
4504 return 0;
4505
4506 list_for_each_entry(rmrru, &dmar_rmrr_units, list) {
4507 rmrr = container_of(rmrru->hdr,
4508 struct acpi_dmar_reserved_memory, header);
4509 if (info->event == BUS_NOTIFY_ADD_DEVICE) {
4510 ret = dmar_insert_dev_scope(info, (void *)(rmrr + 1),
4511 ((void *)rmrr) + rmrr->header.length,
4512 rmrr->segment, rmrru->devices,
4513 rmrru->devices_cnt);
4514 if(ret < 0)
4515 return ret;
4516 } else if (info->event == BUS_NOTIFY_REMOVED_DEVICE) {
4517 dmar_remove_dev_scope(info, rmrr->segment,
4518 rmrru->devices, rmrru->devices_cnt);
4519 }
4520 }
4521
4522 list_for_each_entry(atsru, &dmar_atsr_units, list) {
4523 if (atsru->include_all)
4524 continue;
4525
4526 atsr = container_of(atsru->hdr, struct acpi_dmar_atsr, header);
4527 if (info->event == BUS_NOTIFY_ADD_DEVICE) {
4528 ret = dmar_insert_dev_scope(info, (void *)(atsr + 1),
4529 (void *)atsr + atsr->header.length,
4530 atsr->segment, atsru->devices,
4531 atsru->devices_cnt);
4532 if (ret > 0)
4533 break;
4534 else if(ret < 0)
4535 return ret;
4536 } else if (info->event == BUS_NOTIFY_REMOVED_DEVICE) {
4537 if (dmar_remove_dev_scope(info, atsr->segment,
4538 atsru->devices, atsru->devices_cnt))
4539 break;
4540 }
4541 }
4542
4543 return 0;
4544}

4546/*
4547 * Here we only respond to action of unbound device from driver.
4548 *
4549 * Added device is not attached to its DMAR domain here yet. That will happen
4550 * when mapping the device to iova.
4551 */
4552static int device_notifier(struct notifier_block *nb,
4553 unsigned long action, void *data)
4554{
4555 struct device *dev = data;
4556 struct dmar_domain *domain;
4557
4558 if (iommu_dummy(dev))
4559 return 0;
4560
4561 if (action != BUS_NOTIFY_REMOVED_DEVICE)
4562 return 0;
4563
4564 domain = find_domain(dev);
4565 if (!domain)
4566 return 0;
4567
4568 dmar_remove_one_dev_info(domain, dev);
4569 if (!domain_type_is_vm_or_si(domain) && list_empty(&domain->devices))
4570 domain_exit(domain);
4571
4572 return 0;
4573}

4575static struct notifier_block device_nb = {
4576 .notifier_call = device_notifier,
4577};
4578
4579static int intel_iommu_memory_notifier(struct notifier_block *nb,
4580 unsigned long val, void *v)
4581{
4582 struct memory_notify *mhp = v;
4583 unsigned long long start, end;
4584 unsigned long start_vpfn, last_vpfn;
4585
4586 switch (val) {
4587 case MEM_GOING_ONLINE:
4588 start = mhp->start_pfn << PAGE_SHIFT;
4589 end = ((mhp->start_pfn + mhp->nr_pages) << PAGE_SHIFT) - 1;
4590 if (iommu_domain_identity_map(si_domain, start, end)) {
4591 pr_warn("Failed to build identity map for [%llx-%llx]\n",
4592 start, end);
4593 return NOTIFY_BAD;
4594 }
4595 break;
4596
4597 case MEM_OFFLINE:
4598 case MEM_CANCEL_ONLINE:
4599 start_vpfn = mm_to_dma_pfn(mhp->start_pfn);
4600 last_vpfn = mm_to_dma_pfn(mhp->start_pfn + mhp->nr_pages - 1);
4601 while (start_vpfn <= last_vpfn) {
4602 struct iova *iova;
4603 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
4604 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
4605 struct page *freelist;
4606
4607 iova = find_iova(&si_domain->iovad, start_vpfn);
4608 if (iova == NULL) {
4609 pr_debug("Failed get IOVA for PFN %lx\n",
4610 start_vpfn);
4611 break;
4612 }
4613
4614 iova = split_and_remove_iova(&si_domain->iovad, iova,
4615 start_vpfn, last_vpfn);
4616 if (iova == NULL) {
4617 pr_warn("Failed to split IOVA PFN [%lx-%lx]\n",
4618 start_vpfn, last_vpfn);
4619 return NOTIFY_BAD;
4620 }
4621
4622 freelist = domain_unmap(si_domain, iova->pfn_lo,
4623 iova->pfn_hi);
4624
4625 rcu_read_lock();
4626 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd)
4627 iommu_flush_iotlb_psi(iommu, si_domain,
4628 iova->pfn_lo, iova_size(iova),
4629 !freelist, 0);
4630 rcu_read_unlock();
4631 dma_free_pagelist(freelist);
4632
4633 start_vpfn = iova->pfn_hi + 1;
4634 free_iova_mem(iova);
4635 }
4636 break;
4637 }
4638
4639 return NOTIFY_OK;
4640}

4647static void free_all_cpu_cached_iovas(unsigned int cpu)
4648{

4650
4651 for (i = 0; i < g_num_of_iommus; i++) {

4653 struct dmar_domain *domain;
4654 int did;

4665 }
4666 }

4768int __init intel_iommu_init(void)
4769{
4770 int ret = -ENODEV;
4771 struct dmar_drhd_unit *drhd;
4772 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
4773
4774 /* VT-d is required for a TXT/tboot launch, so enforce that */
4775 force_on = tboot_force_iommu();
4776
4777 if (iommu_init_mempool()) {
4778 if (force_on)
4779 panic("tboot: Failed to initialize iommu memory\n");
4780 return -ENOMEM;
4781 }
4782
4783 down_write(&dmar_global_lock);
4784 if (dmar_table_init()) {
4785 if (force_on)
4786 panic("tboot: Failed to initialize DMAR table\n");
4787 goto out_free_dmar;
4788 }
4789
4790 if (dmar_dev_scope_init() < 0) {
4791 if (force_on)
4792 panic("tboot: Failed to initialize DMAR device scope\n");
4793 goto out_free_dmar;
4794 }
4795
4796 up_write(&dmar_global_lock);
4797
4798 /*
4799 * The bus notifier takes the dmar_global_lock, so lockdep will
4800 * complain later when we register it under the lock.
4801 */
4802 dmar_register_bus_notifier();
4803
4804 down_write(&dmar_global_lock);
4805
4806 if (no_iommu || dmar_disabled) {
4807 /*
4808 * We exit the function here to ensure IOMMU's remapping and
4809 * mempool aren't setup, which means that the IOMMU's PMRs
4810 * won't be disabled via the call to init_dmars(). So disable
4811 * it explicitly here. The PMRs were setup by tboot prior to
4812 * calling SENTER, but the kernel is expected to reset/tear
4813 * down the PMRs.
4814 */
4815 if (intel_iommu_tboot_noforce) {
4816 for_each_iommu(iommu, drhd)
4817 iommu_disable_protect_mem_regions(iommu);
4818 }
4819
4820 /*
4821 * Make sure the IOMMUs are switched off, even when we
4822 * boot into a kexec kernel and the previous kernel left
4823 * them enabled
4824 */
4825 intel_disable_iommus();
4826 goto out_free_dmar;
4827 }
4828
4829 if (list_empty(&dmar_rmrr_units))
4830 pr_info("No RMRR found\n");
4831
4832 if (list_empty(&dmar_atsr_units))
4833 pr_info("No ATSR found\n");
4834
4835 if (dmar_init_reserved_ranges()) {
4836 if (force_on)
4837 panic("tboot: Failed to reserve iommu ranges\n");
4838 goto out_free_reserved_range;
4839 }
4840
4841 init_no_remapping_devices();
4842
4843 ret = init_dmars();
4844 if (ret) {
4845 if (force_on)
4846 panic("tboot: Failed to initialize DMARs\n");
4847 pr_err("Initialization failed\n");
4848 goto out_free_reserved_range;
4849 }
4850 up_write(&dmar_global_lock);
4851 pr_info("Intel(R) Virtualization Technology for Directed I/O\n");
4852
4853#if defined(CONFIG_X86) && defined(CONFIG_SWIOTLB)
4854 swiotlb = 0;
4855#endif
4856 dma_ops = &intel_dma_ops;
4857
4858 init_iommu_pm_ops();
4859
4860 for_each_active_iommu(iommu, drhd) {
4861 iommu_device_sysfs_add(&iommu->iommu, NULL,
4862 intel_iommu_groups,
4863 "%s", iommu->name);
4864 iommu_device_set_ops(&iommu->iommu, &intel_iommu_ops);
4865 iommu_device_register(&iommu->iommu);
4866 }
4867
4868 bus_set_iommu(&pci_bus_type, &intel_iommu_ops);
4869 bus_register_notifier(&pci_bus_type, &device_nb);
4870 if (si_domain && !hw_pass_through)
4871 register_memory_notifier(&intel_iommu_memory_nb);
4872 cpuhp_setup_state(CPUHP_IOMMU_INTEL_DEAD, "iommu/intel:dead", NULL,
4873 intel_iommu_cpu_dead);
4874 intel_iommu_enabled = 1;
4875
4876 return 0;
4877
4878out_free_reserved_range:
4879 put_iova_domain(&reserved_iova_list);
4880out_free_dmar:
4881 intel_iommu_free_dmars();
4882 up_write(&dmar_global_lock);
4883 iommu_exit_mempool();
4884 return ret;
4885}

4947static int md_domain_init(struct dmar_domain *domain, int guest_width)
4948{
4949 int adjust_width;
4950
4951 init_iova_domain(&domain->iovad, VTD_PAGE_SIZE, IOVA_START_PFN);
4952 domain_reserve_special_ranges(domain);
4953
4954 /* calculate AGAW */
4955 domain->gaw = guest_width;
4956 adjust_width = guestwidth_to_adjustwidth(guest_width);
4957 domain->agaw = width_to_agaw(adjust_width);
4958
4959 domain->iommu_coherency = 0;
4960 domain->iommu_snooping = 0;
4961 domain->iommu_superpage = 0;
4962 domain->max_addr = 0;
4963
4964 /* always allocate the top pgd */
4965 domain->pgd = (struct dma_pte *)alloc_pgtable_page(domain->nid);
4966 if (!domain->pgd)
4967 return -ENOMEM;
4968 domain_flush_cache(domain, domain->pgd, PAGE_SIZE);
4969 return 0;
4970}

5004
5005static int intel_iommu_attach_device(struct iommu_domain *domain,
5006 struct device *dev)
5007{
5008 struct dmar_domain *dmar_domain = to_dmar_domain(domain);
5009 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
5010 int addr_width;
5011 u8 bus, devfn;
5012
5013 if (device_is_rmrr_locked(dev)) {
5014 dev_warn(dev, "Device is ineligible for IOMMU domain attach due to platform RMRR requirement. Contact your platform vendor.\n");
5015 return -EPERM;
5016 }
5017
5018 /* normally dev is not mapped */
5019 if (unlikely(domain_context_mapped(dev))) {
5020 struct dmar_domain *old_domain;
5021
5022 old_domain = find_domain(dev);
5023 if (old_domain) {
5024 rcu_read_lock();
5025 dmar_remove_one_dev_info(old_domain, dev);
5026 rcu_read_unlock();
5027
5028 if (!domain_type_is_vm_or_si(old_domain) &&
5029 list_empty(&old_domain->devices))
5030 domain_exit(old_domain);
5031 }
5032 }
5033
5034 iommu = device_to_iommu(dev, &bus, &devfn);
5035 if (!iommu)
5036 return -ENODEV;
5037
5038 /* check if this iommu agaw is sufficient for max mapped address */
5039 addr_width = agaw_to_width(iommu->agaw);
5040 if (addr_width > cap_mgaw(iommu->cap))
5041 addr_width = cap_mgaw(iommu->cap);
5042
5043 if (dmar_domain->max_addr > (1LL << addr_width)) {
5044 pr_err("%s: iommu width (%d) is not "
5045 "sufficient for the mapped address (%llx)\n",
5046 __func__, addr_width, dmar_domain->max_addr);
5047 return -EFAULT;
5048 }
5049 dmar_domain->gaw = addr_width;
5050
5051 /*
5052 * Knock out extra levels of page tables if necessary
5053 */
5054 while (iommu->agaw < dmar_domain->agaw) {
5055 struct dma_pte *pte;
5056
5057 pte = dmar_domain->pgd;
5058 if (dma_pte_present(pte)) {
5059 dmar_domain->pgd = (struct dma_pte *)
5060 phys_to_virt(dma_pte_addr(pte));
5061 free_pgtable_page(pte);
5062 }
5063 dmar_domain->agaw--;
5064 }
5065
5066 return domain_add_dev_info(dmar_domain, dev);
5067}

5069static void intel_iommu_detach_device(struct iommu_domain *domain,
5070 struct device *dev)
5071{
5072 dmar_remove_one_dev_info(to_dmar_domain(domain), dev);
5073}
5074
5075static int intel_iommu_map(struct iommu_domain *domain,
5076 unsigned long iova, phys_addr_t hpa,
5077 size_t size, int iommu_prot)
5078{
5079 struct dmar_domain *dmar_domain = to_dmar_domain(domain);
5080 u64 max_addr;
5081 int prot = 0;
5082 int ret;
5083
5084 if (iommu_prot & IOMMU_READ)
5085 prot |= DMA_PTE_READ;
5086 if (iommu_prot & IOMMU_WRITE)
5087 prot |= DMA_PTE_WRITE;
5088 if ((iommu_prot & IOMMU_CACHE) && dmar_domain->iommu_snooping)
5089 prot |= DMA_PTE_SNP;
5090
5091 max_addr = iova + size;
5092 if (dmar_domain->max_addr < max_addr) {
5093 u64 end;
5094
5095 /* check if minimum agaw is sufficient for mapped address */
5096 end = __DOMAIN_MAX_ADDR(dmar_domain->gaw) + 1;
5097 if (end < max_addr) {
5098 pr_err("%s: iommu width (%d) is not "
5099 "sufficient for the mapped address (%llx)\n",
5100 __func__, dmar_domain->gaw, max_addr);
5101 return -EFAULT;
5102 }
5103 dmar_domain->max_addr = max_addr;
5104 }
5105 /* Round up size to next multiple of PAGE_SIZE, if it and
5106 the low bits of hpa would take us onto the next page */
5107 size = aligned_nrpages(hpa, size);
5108 ret = domain_pfn_mapping(dmar_domain, iova >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT,
5109 hpa >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT, size, prot);
5110 return ret;
5111}
5112
5113static size_t intel_iommu_unmap(struct iommu_domain *domain,
5114 unsigned long iova, size_t size)
5115{
5116 struct dmar_domain *dmar_domain = to_dmar_domain(domain);
5117 struct page *freelist = NULL;
5118 unsigned long start_pfn, last_pfn;
5119 unsigned int npages;
5120 int iommu_id, level = 0;
5121
5122 /* Cope with horrid API which requires us to unmap more than the
5123 size argument if it happens to be a large-page mapping. */
5124 BUG_ON(!pfn_to_dma_pte(dmar_domain, iova >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT, &level));
5125
5126 if (size < VTD_PAGE_SIZE << level_to_offset_bits(level))
5127 size = VTD_PAGE_SIZE << level_to_offset_bits(level);
5128
5129 start_pfn = iova >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT;
5130 last_pfn = (iova + size - 1) >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT;
5131
5132 freelist = domain_unmap(dmar_domain, start_pfn, last_pfn);
5133
5134 npages = last_pfn - start_pfn + 1;
5135
5136 for_each_domain_iommu(iommu_id, dmar_domain)
5137 iommu_flush_iotlb_psi(g_iommus[iommu_id], dmar_domain,
5138 start_pfn, npages, !freelist, 0);
5139
5140 dma_free_pagelist(freelist);
5141
5142 if (dmar_domain->max_addr == iova + size)
5143 dmar_domain->max_addr = iova;
5144
5145 return size;
5146}

5148static phys_addr_t intel_iommu_iova_to_phys(struct iommu_domain *domain,
5149 dma_addr_t iova)
5150{
5151 struct dmar_domain *dmar_domain = to_dmar_domain(domain);
5152 struct dma_pte *pte;
5153 int level = 0;
5154 u64 phys = 0;
5155
5156 pte = pfn_to_dma_pte(dmar_domain, iova >> VTD_PAGE_SHIFT, &level);
5157 if (pte)
5158 phys = dma_pte_addr(pte);
5159
5160 return phys;
5161}

5247#ifdef CONFIG_INTEL_IOMMU_SVM
5248#define MAX_NR_PASID_BITS (20)
5249static inline unsigned long intel_iommu_get_pts(struct intel_iommu *iommu)
5250{
5251 /*
5252 * Convert ecap_pss to extend context entry pts encoding, also
5253 * respect the soft pasid_max value set by the iommu.
5254 * - number of PASID bits = ecap_pss + 1
5255 * - number of PASID table entries = 2^(pts + 5)
5256 * Therefore, pts = ecap_pss - 4
5257 * e.g. KBL ecap_pss = 0x13, PASID has 20 bits, pts = 15
5258 */
5259 if (ecap_pss(iommu->ecap) < 5)
5260 return 0;
5261
5262 /* pasid_max is encoded as actual number of entries not the bits */
5263 return find_first_bit((unsigned long *)&iommu->pasid_max,
5264 MAX_NR_PASID_BITS) - 5;
5265}
5266
5267int intel_iommu_enable_pasid(struct intel_iommu *iommu, struct intel_svm_dev *sdev)
5268{
5269 struct device_domain_info *info;
5270 struct context_entry *context;
5271 struct dmar_domain *domain;
5272 unsigned long flags;
5273 u64 ctx_lo;
5274 int ret;
5275
5276 domain = get_valid_domain_for_dev(sdev->dev);
5277 if (!domain)
5278 return -EINVAL;
5279
5280 spin_lock_irqsave(&device_domain_lock, flags);
5281 spin_lock(&iommu->lock);
5282
5283 ret = -EINVAL;
5284 info = sdev->dev->archdata.iommu;
5285 if (!info || !info->pasid_supported)
5286 goto out;
5287
5288 context = iommu_context_addr(iommu, info->bus, info->devfn, 0);
5289 if (WARN_ON(!context))
5290 goto out;
5291
5292 ctx_lo = context[0].lo;
5293
5294 sdev->did = domain->iommu_did[iommu->seq_id];
5295 sdev->sid = PCI_DEVID(info->bus, info->devfn);
5296
5297 if (!(ctx_lo & CONTEXT_PASIDE)) {
5298 if (iommu->pasid_state_table)
5299 context[1].hi = (u64)virt_to_phys(iommu->pasid_state_table);
5300 context[1].lo = (u64)virt_to_phys(iommu->pasid_table) |
5301 intel_iommu_get_pts(iommu);
5302
5303 wmb();
5304 /* CONTEXT_TT_MULTI_LEVEL and CONTEXT_TT_DEV_IOTLB are both
5305 * extended to permit requests-with-PASID if the PASIDE bit
5306 * is set. which makes sense. For CONTEXT_TT_PASS_THROUGH,
5307 * however, the PASIDE bit is ignored and requests-with-PASID
5308 * are unconditionally blocked. Which makes less sense.
5309 * So convert from CONTEXT_TT_PASS_THROUGH to one of the new
5310 * "guest mode" translation types depending on whether ATS
5311 * is available or not. Annoyingly, we can't use the new
5312 * modes *unless* PASIDE is set. */
5313 if ((ctx_lo & CONTEXT_TT_MASK) == (CONTEXT_TT_PASS_THROUGH << 2)) {
5314 ctx_lo &= ~CONTEXT_TT_MASK;
5315 if (info->ats_supported)
5316 ctx_lo |= CONTEXT_TT_PT_PASID_DEV_IOTLB << 2;
5317 else
5318 ctx_lo |= CONTEXT_TT_PT_PASID << 2;
5319 }
5320 ctx_lo |= CONTEXT_PASIDE;
5321 if (iommu->pasid_state_table)
5322 ctx_lo |= CONTEXT_DINVE;
5323 if (info->pri_supported)
5324 ctx_lo |= CONTEXT_PRS;
5325 context[0].lo = ctx_lo;
5326 wmb();
5327 iommu->flush.flush_context(iommu, sdev->did, sdev->sid,
5328 DMA_CCMD_MASK_NOBIT,
5329 DMA_CCMD_DEVICE_INVL);
5330 }
5331
5332 /* Enable PASID support in the device, if it wasn't already */
5333 if (!info->pasid_enabled)
5334 iommu_enable_dev_iotlb(info);
5335
5336 if (info->ats_enabled) {
5337 sdev->dev_iotlb = 1;
5338 sdev->qdep = info->ats_qdep;
5339 if (sdev->qdep >= QI_DEV_EIOTLB_MAX_INVS)
5340 sdev->qdep = 0;
5341 }
5342 ret = 0;
5343
5344 out:
5345 spin_unlock(&iommu->lock);
5346 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&device_domain_lock, flags);
5347
5348 return ret;
5349}

5351struct intel_iommu *intel_svm_device_to_iommu(struct device *dev)

5353 struct intel_iommu *iommu;
5354 u8 bus, devfn;

5357 dev_warn(dev,

5438static void quirk_calpella_no_shadow_gtt(struct pci_dev *dev)
5439{
5440 unsigned short ggc;
5441
5442 if (pci_read_config_word(dev, GGC, &ggc))
5443 return;
5444
5445 if (!(ggc & GGC_MEMORY_VT_ENABLED)) {
5446 pr_info("BIOS has allocated no shadow GTT; disabling IOMMU for graphics\n");
5447 dmar_map_gfx = 0;
5448 } else if (dmar_map_gfx) {
5449 /* we have to ensure the gfx device is idle before we flush */
5450 pr_info("Disabling batched IOTLB flush on Ironlake\n");
5451 intel_iommu_strict = 1;
5452 }
5453}

5459/* On Tylersburg chipsets, some BIOSes have been known to enable the
5460 ISOCH DMAR unit for the Azalia sound device, but not give it any
5461 TLB entries, which causes it to deadlock. Check for that. We do
5462 this in a function called from init_dmars(), instead of in a PCI
5463 quirk, because we don't want to print the obnoxious "BIOS broken"
5464 message if VT-d is actually disabled.
5465*/
5466static void __init check_tylersburg_isoch(void)
5467{
5468 struct pci_dev *pdev;
5469 uint32_t vtisochctrl;
5470
5471 /* If there's no Azalia in the system anyway, forget it. */
5472 pdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL, 0x3a3e, NULL);
5473 if (!pdev)
5474 return;
5475 pci_dev_put(pdev);
5476
5477 /* System Management Registers. Might be hidden, in which case
5478 we can't do the sanity check. But that's OK, because the
5479 known-broken BIOSes _don't_ actually hide it, so far. */
5480 pdev = pci_get_device(PCI_VENDOR_ID_INTEL, 0x342e, NULL);
5481 if (!pdev)
5482 return;
5483
5484 if (pci_read_config_dword(pdev, 0x188, &vtisochctrl)) {
5485 pci_dev_put(pdev);
5486 return;
5487 }
5488
5489 pci_dev_put(pdev);
5490
5491 /* If Azalia DMA is routed to the non-isoch DMAR unit, fine. */
5492 if (vtisochctrl & 1)
5493 return;
5494
5495 /* Drop all bits other than the number of TLB entries */
5496 vtisochctrl &= 0x1c;
5497
5498 /* If we have the recommended number of TLB entries (16), fine. */
5499 if (vtisochctrl == 0x10)
5500 return;
5501
5502 /* Zero TLB entries? You get to ride the short bus to school. */
5503 if (!vtisochctrl) {
5504 WARN(1, "Your BIOS is broken; DMA routed to ISOCH DMAR unit but no TLB space.\n"
5505 "BIOS vendor: %s; Ver: %s; Product Version: %s\n",
5506 dmi_get_system_info(DMI_BIOS_VENDOR),
5507 dmi_get_system_info(DMI_BIOS_VERSION),
5508 dmi_get_system_info(DMI_PRODUCT_VERSION));
5509 iommu_identity_mapping |= IDENTMAP_AZALIA;
5510 return;
5511 }
5512
5513 pr_warn("Recommended TLB entries for ISOCH unit is 16; your BIOS set %d\n",
5514 vtisochctrl);
5515}
